      "stem": "下列哪一項符合「Radiobiology clinical translation」的重點？",
      "stem_en": "Which point best matches \"Clinical translation of radiobiology\"?",
      "ans": "B",
      "exp": "重點：Low LET photons 很依賴 indirect free radical damage；oxygen 會把 radical-induced damage 固定成 permanent lesion。Hypoxia 時這些 lesion 較可能被 repair，因此 cell kill 下降。Photon OER 約 2.5-3，代表 hypoxic cells 可能需要約 2.5-3 倍 dose 才達到相同效果。",
      "exp_en": "Key point: Low-LET photons depend heavily on indirect free-radical damage. Oxygen fixes radical-induced damage into permanent lesions. Under hypoxia, these lesions are more likely to be repaired, reducing cell kill. Photon OER is about 2.5-3, meaning hypoxic cells may need 2.5-3 times the dose to achieve the same effect.",
      "A": "電子束: 直接游離輻射，能量 6-20 MeV，用於皮膚、乳房疤痕、chest wall boost。",
      "A_en": "Electrons: Directly ionizing, 6-20 MeV - used for skin, breast scar, chest wall boost.",
      "B": "Low LET photons 很依賴 indirect free radical damage；oxygen 會把 radical-induced damage 固定成 permanent lesion。Hypoxia 時這些 lesion 較可能被 repair，因此 cell kill 下降。Photon OER 約 2.5-3，代表 hypoxic cells 可能需要約 2.5-3 倍 dose 才達到相同效果。",
      "B_en": "Low-LET photons depend heavily on indirect free-radical damage. Oxygen fixes radical-induced damage into permanent lesions. Under hypoxia, these lesions are more likely to be repaired, reducing cell kill. Photon OER is about 2.5-3, meaning hypoxic cells may need 2.5-3 times the dose to achieve the same effect.",
      "C": "Gy (灰): 吸收劑量的 SI 單位，1 Gy = 1 J/kg。臨床通常以每日 分次 (fraction) 給予，如 2 Gy × 30 次 = 60 Gy。",
      "C_en": "Gray (Gy): SI unit of absorbed dose; 1 Gy = 1 J/kg. Clinical RT is delivered in daily fractions , e.g., 2 Gy × 30 = 60 Gy total.",
      "D": "臨床適用: 兒童（減少發育中組織的整體劑量）、顱底、脊索瘤、眼部黑色素瘤。",
      "D_en": "Clinical use: Pediatrics (reduce integral dose to developing tissues), skull base, chordoma, ocular melanoma."
