      "B": "低級別膠質瘤影像陷阱 ：低級別膠質瘤不一定增強；若看似低級別的病灶出現增強，尤其周邊結節樣增強或壞死，應懷疑高級別轉化或本來就是高級別病灶。",
      "B_en": "Low-grade glioma imaging pitfall : low-grade gliomas may be non-enhancing; enhancement, especially peripheral nodular enhancement or necrosis, increases suspicion for high-grade transformation or an intrinsically higher-grade lesion.",
      "C": "SRS alone 與 WBRT 的 trade-off 很穩定：SRS alone cognition better, OS generally similar, but local/distant brain failure higher；WBRT 則 intracranial control better, cognition worse, OS usually not improved。",
      "C_en": "The trade-off between SRS alone and WBRT is stable: SRS alone has better cognition and generally similar overall survival, but higher local and distant brain failure; WBRT has better intracranial control, worse cognition, and usually no overall-survival improvement.",
      "D": "膠質瘤是中樞神經系統最重要的原發性腫瘤，也是成人原發性中樞神經系統惡性腫瘤最常見的來源。膠質瘤來自神經膠質細胞，也就是神經系統的支持細胞，包括星形膠質細胞、少突膠質細胞與小膠質細胞。",
      "D_en": "Gliomas are the most important primary tumors of the central nervous system and represent the most common source of adult primary CNS malignancy. They arise from glial cells, the supportive cells of the nervous system, including astrocytes, oligodendrocytes, and microglial cells."
