      "B_en": "Presentation : hematochezia is most common; changes in bowel habits, diarrhea/constipation, narrow stool, tenesmus, incomplete evacuation, pain, weight loss, fatigue, abdominal pain/distension; very locally advanced disease may cause urinary symptoms.",
