      "B_en": "BCC: Pearly pink or skin-colored bump, often in sun-exposed areas; Subtypes include nodular, superficial, pigmented, morpheaform, and basosquamous; morpheaform/infiltrative/micronodular/basosquamous patterns are more aggressive",
