      "stem": "關於「Rhabdomyosarcoma：部位、風險分層、VAC/VAC-VI、RT 適應症與劑量」，下列何者正確？",
      "stem_en": "Which statement is correct about \"Rhabdomyosarcoma: sites, risk stratification, VAC/VAC-VI, RT indications, and dose\"?",
      "ans": "B",
      "exp": "重點：Rhabdomyosarcoma 是最常見 pediatric soft tissue tumor，每年約 400-500 cases，slight male predominance 1.4:1，peak age 3-5 years，70% cases before age 10。主要 histology 包括 embryonal RMS 和 alveolar RMS；alveolar/fusion-positive 通常 prognosis 較差。",
      "exp_en": "Key point: Rhabdomyosarcoma is the most common pediatric soft tissue tumor, with about 400-500 cases per year. There is slight male predominance, about 1.4:1. Peak age is 3-5 years, and 70% occur before age 10. Main histologies are embryonal RMS and alveolar RMS; alveolar/fusion-positive disease has worse prognosis.",
      "A": "Hemoptysis / airway obstruction: 急性 airway compromise 先 bronchoscopy/stent/laser; 穩定後控制 hemoptysis、cough、dyspnea; 10 Gy ×1、17 Gy/2、20 Gy/5、30 Gy/10、40-45 Gy/15",
      "A_en": "Hemoptysis / airway obstruction: For acute airway compromise, bronchoscopy, stent, or laser first.; After stabilization, radiotherapy controls hemoptysis, cough, and dyspnea.; 10 Gy ×1, 17 Gy in 2 fractions, 20 Gy in 5 fractions, 30 Gy in 10 fractions, 40-45 Gy in 15 fractions.",
      "B": "Rhabdomyosarcoma 是最常見 pediatric soft tissue tumor，每年約 400-500 cases，slight male predominance 1.4:1，peak age 3-5 years，70% cases before age 10。主要 histology 包括 embryonal RMS 和 alveolar RMS；alveolar/fusion-positive 通常 prognosis 較差。",
      "B_en": "Rhabdomyosarcoma is the most common pediatric soft tissue tumor, with about 400-500 cases per year. There is slight male predominance, about 1.4:1. Peak age is 3-5 years, and 70% occur before age 10. Main histologies are embryonal RMS and alveolar RMS; alveolar/fusion-positive disease has worse prognosis.",
      "C": "Cord compression 定義是任何 radiographic compression of spinal cord 或 cauda equina。可分 epidural compression，由 tumor 或 bone fragment 造成；intradural disease；intradural extramedullary，例如 leptomeningeal disease；intramedullary，即 spinal cord 內 tumor deposit。",
      "C_en": "Cord compression is any radiographic compression of the spinal cord or cauda equina. It can be epidural compression from tumor or bone fragment, intradural disease, intradural extramedullary disease such as leptomeningeal disease, or intramedullary tumor deposit within the spinal cord.",
      "D": "Radiation emergency 不等於一定要立刻 RT。核心原則是：先評估是否真正急危、是否需要 tissue diagnosis、是否有 prior RT、是否需要先手術/介入處置。",
      "D_en": "A radiation emergency does not automatically mean immediate radiotherapy. The first step is to decide whether the situation is truly urgent, whether tissue diagnosis is needed, whether the patient has had prior radiotherapy, and whether surgery or an interventional procedure should come first."
