      "exp": "重點：Ewing 50% central，包含 pelvis 45%、chest wall 35%、spine 10%；50% extremities，常在 diaphysis。Mnemonic：EG-MODE，Epiphysis = Giant cell tumor；Metaphysis = Osteosarcoma；Diaphysis = Ewing。",
      "exp_en": "Key point: About half of Ewing tumors are central-pelvis 45%, chest wall 35%, spine 10%-and half are extremity tumors, often diaphyseal. The mnemonic EG-MODE: epiphysis = giant cell tumor; metaphysis = osteosarcoma; diaphysis = Ewing.",
      "A": "Radiation emergency 不等於一定要立刻 RT。核心原則是：先評估是否真正急危、是否需要 tissue diagnosis、是否有 prior RT、是否需要先手術/介入處置。",
      "A_en": "A radiation emergency does not automatically mean immediate radiotherapy. The first step is to decide whether the situation is truly urgent, whether tissue diagnosis is needed, whether the patient has had prior radiotherapy, and whether surgery or an interventional procedure should come first.",
