      "B_en": "Spine SBRT: Select low-instability, no symptomatic compression, good performance status patients.; Improves complete pain response; strict cord constraints are essential.; Examples include 24 Gy in 2 fractions.",
      "C": "Complicated: 有 pathologic fracture、spinal cord/cauda equina compression；臨床上也常把 soft tissue component、weight-bearing bone high fracture risk 納入 complicated",
      "C_en": "Complicated: Pathologic fracture, spinal cord or cauda equina compression; in practice, soft-tissue component and high fracture risk in weight-bearing bone are also often treated as complicated.",
      "D": "Ewing 50% central，包含 pelvis 45%、chest wall 35%、spine 10%；50% extremities，常在 diaphysis。Mnemonic：EG-MODE，Epiphysis = Giant cell tumor；Metaphysis = Osteosarcoma；Diaphysis = Ewing。",
      "D_en": "About half of Ewing tumors are central-pelvis 45%, chest wall 35%, spine 10%-and half are extremity tumors, often diaphyseal. The mnemonic EG-MODE: epiphysis = giant cell tumor; metaphysis = osteosarcoma; diaphysis = Ewing."
