      "B": "Cord compression 定義是任何 radiographic compression of spinal cord 或 cauda equina。可分 epidural compression，由 tumor 或 bone fragment 造成；intradural disease；intradural extramedullary，例如 leptomeningeal disease；intramedullary，即 spinal cord 內 tumor deposit。",
      "B_en": "Cord compression is any radiographic compression of the spinal cord or cauda equina. It can be epidural compression from tumor or bone fragment, intradural disease, intradural extramedullary disease such as leptomeningeal disease, or intramedullary tumor deposit within the spinal cord.",
      "C": "Wilms tumor 佔 childhood cancers 約 6%，美國每年約 500 cases，是 children 最常見 abdominal tumor。Median age 3-4 years，75% 在 age 5 前診斷；4-8% 是 bilateral tumors，bilateral cases median age 更低，約 2-3 years。",
      "C_en": "Wilms tumor accounts for about 6% of childhood cancers, with about 500 cases per year in the United States, and is the most common abdominal tumor in children. Median age is 3-4 years; 75% are diagnosed before age 5. About 4-8% are bilateral, and bilateral cases present earlier, around age 2-3 years.",
      "D": "2021 WHO classification 依三個因素：anatomic site、WHO grade、molecular features。Anatomic site 包括 supratentorial、posterior fossa、spinal。WHO grade：grade 1 subependymoma；grade 2 classic/differentiated and myxopapillary ependymoma；grade 3 anaplastic。",
      "D_en": "The 2021 WHO classification uses anatomic site, WHO grade, and molecular features. Sites include supratentorial, posterior fossa, and spinal. Grades include grade 1 subependymoma, grade 2 classic/differentiated and myxopapillary ependymoma, and grade 3 anaplastic ependymoma."
