      "ans": "D",
      "exp": "重點：MSCC suspected 時 first step 是 steroids，作為 definitive treatment 前的 bridge。Mechanism 是減少 inflammation 與 cord edema，並對 multiple myeloma/lymphoma 有 direct oncolytic effects。要 monitor hyperglycemia、hypertension，並用 PPI 或 H2 blocker 做 GI prophylaxis。",
      "exp_en": "Key point: When MSCC is suspected, the first step is steroids as a bridge to definitive treatment. Steroids reduce inflammation and cord edema and may have direct oncolytic effects in multiple myeloma and lymphoma. Monitor hyperglycemia and hypertension, and provide gastrointestinal prophylaxis with a PPI or H2 blocker.",
      "A": "2021 WHO classification 依三個因素：anatomic site、WHO grade、molecular features。Anatomic site 包括 supratentorial、posterior fossa、spinal。WHO grade：grade 1 subependymoma；grade 2 classic/differentiated and myxopapillary ependymoma；grade 3 anaplastic。",
      "A_en": "The 2021 WHO classification uses anatomic site, WHO grade, and molecular features. Sites include supratentorial, posterior fossa, and spinal. Grades include grade 1 subependymoma, grade 2 classic/differentiated and myxopapillary ependymoma, and grade 3 anaplastic ependymoma.",
      "B": "Wilms tumor 是 embryonic kidney tumor，classically triphasic，包括 blastemal、epithelial、stromal elements。大多數 sporadic，但 10-13% 與 congenital anomalies 相關，如 WAGR、Denys-Drash、Beckwith-Wiedemann syndrome。",
      "B_en": "Wilms tumor is an embryonic kidney tumor and is classically triphasic with blastemal, epithelial, and stromal elements. Most are sporadic, but 10-13% are associated with congenital anomalies such as WAGR, Denys-Drash, and Beckwith-Wiedemann syndrome.",
      "C": "Rhabdomyosarcoma 是最常見 pediatric soft tissue tumor，每年約 400-500 cases，slight male predominance 1.4:1，peak age 3-5 years，70% cases before age 10。主要 histology 包括 embryonal RMS 和 alveolar RMS；alveolar/fusion-positive 通常 prognosis 較差。",
      "C_en": "Rhabdomyosarcoma is the most common pediatric soft tissue tumor, with about 400-500 cases per year. There is slight male predominance, about 1.4:1. Peak age is 3-5 years, and 70% occur before age 10. Main histologies are embryonal RMS and alveolar RMS; alveolar/fusion-positive disease has worse prognosis.",
      "D": "MSCC suspected 時 first step 是 steroids，作為 definitive treatment 前的 bridge。Mechanism 是減少 inflammation 與 cord edema，並對 multiple myeloma/lymphoma 有 direct oncolytic effects。要 monitor hyperglycemia、hypertension，並用 PPI 或 H2 blocker 做 GI prophylaxis。",
      "D_en": "When MSCC is suspected, the first step is steroids as a bridge to definitive treatment. Steroids reduce inflammation and cord edema and may have direct oncolytic effects in multiple myeloma and lymphoma. Monitor hyperglycemia and hypertension, and provide gastrointestinal prophylaxis with a PPI or H2 blocker."
